This instructor was awesome. Started off slow but got better as the semester continued. I learned information that I will use in my internship and job.

I had Kat her 1st semester at ISU. She definitely has room for improvement; isn't really on the same level as other 300 level professors. Classes are lectures with small group work frequently, but they are kind of juvenile. I didn't take away much from the class. Book not completely necessary, takes random attendance.

This was one of the worst classes that I've ever taken. Not only was it boring, but she didn't know what she was talking about. She used slides straight from the text book and had to check back over her notes repeatedly, making it take 10 minutes to go over each slide. Also the exams were too hard for such easy material. DONT TAKE THIS CLASS
